  "text": "Taking into account studies such as Selva's research, Sergio Arboleda University is carrying out its second satellite mission, called Libertad 2, which consists of the development and deployment of a nano-satellite of 3 units designed under the standard of CubeSat. This mission aims wto validate the development of a prototype of RS system, which will open the field for academic research in Colombia, based on images that it could get; these investigations can focus on the analysis of use of the land for agriculture, water resources, planning of urban growth, among others. This article focuses on the identification of the characteristics, requirements and restrictions, which must be considered in the design of an RS system for CubeSat satellites, in order to serve as a starting point for the development of the main payload of the Libertad 2 mission. Triana, J.S., Bautista, S. and González, F.A.D. Figure 1. CubeSat subsystem's architecture [CITATION_1] ).",
